_resumeContext is a single per-thread slot. When an interrupt fiber itself
suspends mid-flight (contended thread_lock in sigexc_enter, a blocking
interrupted continuation), its own park OVERWRITES the slot; the later
jumpToResume then setcontext()s a stale/garbage context -- the #114 SEGV,
captured live under the stage-0 fuzzer with a full backtrace:
  setcontext <- _handleInterruptEnterForCurrentThread <- InterruptEnter::processCall

InterruptContext gains savedResumeContext (captured next to savedStack at
stacking time in doWork); jumpToResume takes the explicit context to restore.
Nested interrupts get the right copy per level by construction.

This kills the single-slot clobber shape of #114; the abandoned-frame stack
lifetime shape (stacked interrupt freeing a suspended interrupt fiber's
stack) remains for stage 3.
