One per-thread run-state {Idle, Running, Parking, Parked, Ready, Terminated}
written through a single legality-asserting transition function at every
existing _running/_suspended flip site (shadow mode: deriving from the flags,
not yet driving them -- stage 2b flips authority). Wake arms/disarms/deliveries/
drops, interrupt push/pop, rerun deferrals and impersonation pins are recorded
as events on a 32-entry per-thread ring tape.

- violations (illegal transition or state/flag mismatch) dump the tape at error
  level and survive; DSERVER_MSTATE_ABORT=1 makes them fatal
- duct-tape panic() now dumps the current microthread's tape via a new
  current_thread_dump_state_tape hook (replaces printf archaeology)
- a0-gate: fuzz legs run with DSERVER_MSTATE_ABORT=1 (violation = crash = RED);
  all synth legs log at err level and grep the server log for MSTATE VIOLATION

