From 1b48f1544e65595edf944bdea7bf9406fc0591cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ilya Gulya <ilya@gulya.me>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 04:04:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] A0-ARCH stage 2b: flip run-state authority to MicroState

_running/_suspended stop existing as fields: _isRunningLocked() (Running |
Parking | impersonation pin) and _isSuspendedLocked() (Parking | Parked |
Ready) are derived views of _microState, updated ONLY by the transition
function. The impersonation lockout gets its own _impersonationPin field
instead of being smuggled through _running=true on a non-running thread.

doWork captures preDispatchParked before the Running transition (the dispatch-
decision logic needs the pre-dispatch view; there is no lingering flag residue
to read anymore); suspend()'s park-vs-resumed discriminator and the inline
paths' suspend-contract checks read the state field directly. The 2a flag-
consistency asserts are gone (tautological now) -- the legality table is the
contract.

Boot smoke green, zero violations. Task #116 stage 2b.
