First 2b fuzz finding, caught by the tape in one gdb walk: a spurious dispatch
of a Parked thread went Parked->Running("dispatch-stale")->Idle("done") --
doneWorking's Parking-only repark discriminator lost the park that the old
_suspended flag carried implicitly. The next genuine wake then dropped as
"no-park" and the thread wedged forever (fuzz seeds 1-3 all wedged launchd at
boot; tape[255..257] on the wedged launchd named the exact sequence).

