Subject: [PATCH] A0-ARCH stage 2c: route all XNU wait-state writes through one
 funnel; delete dtape_thread_entering

Every write of the TH_WAIT/TH_RUN/TH_UNINT/TH_TERMINATE bits and wait_result now
goes through xnu_wait_state_write() in duct-tape/src/thread.c as a NAMED
transition (destroy / sigexc-abort / dying / unblock / mark-wait / kthread-birth /
start-assert-wait / user-suspension-wait / waitq prepost early-out), reported to
the server via the new thread_xwait_transition hook and recorded on the thread's
run-state tape as StateEvent::XnuWait (aux8 = new bits, aux64 = old bits<<32 |
wait_result). Violations (unblock of a non-waiting thread, double mark-wait,
mark-wait on a terminating thread) get the MSTATE VIOLATION treatment: error log
(gate-grepable), tape dump, abort under DSERVER_MSTATE_ABORT=1.

dtape_thread_entering() is DELETED -- its unconditional "entering => cannot be
waiting" TH_WAIT clobber was the A0 disease, and doWork's preserveWaitState
skip-dance existed only to dodge it. The skip-condition is now the assertion the
spec asked for: an unambiguous fresh-call dispatch (doWork + both inline paths)
asserts the guest thread is NOT waiting; a stranded TH_WAIT is recovery-cleared
exactly like entering used to, but LOUDLY (dtape_thread_clear_stranded_wait +
_strandedWaitViolationLocked). Part-3e re-park loop iterations are taped
(xwait-repark-still-waiting). TH_RUN/block_hint stay write-only diagnostics;
dtape_thread_exiting keeps its TH_RUN clear untapped (caller holds the Thread
lock). Birth init in dtape_thread_create stays outside the funnel (owning Thread
mid-construction).

Task #116 stage 2c per tests/A0-ARCH-REDESIGN-SPEC.md; gate running.
