compensates a KERN_NOT_WAITING signal (\_kwq_mark_interruped_wakeup 'interrupt
post' / the firstfit redrive), so XNU's waiter-side discard of the committed
retval is deliberate -- honoring it delivers the same grant twice and desyncs
the mutex seq protocol (captured live: consumer cycling EINTR mutexwait retries
at storm rate against a mutex nobody owns, producer parked forever). The wedge
that motivated fix 2 was actually the timerfd stale-deadline bug (fix 3).
